You have 2 mistakes which are giving wrong outputs for both inputs (1 and 3).
### 1. Initialize `currentSequence` with 1
You should initialize `currentSequence` inside the statement `if (prev == 0)`. So, it also counts as the first element. (the cause for the counting 4s three).
The updated `if` statement will be:
```java
if (prev == 0) {
   prev = value;
   currentSequence = 1;
   continue;
}
```

### 2. Also, check for the longest Sequence after the loop
The body of the loop does not execute when the input is `0`. So, it does not update `longestSequecne` for the last number (or sequence).
The same condition will be added after the loop.
```java
if (currentSequence &gt; longestSequence) {
     longestSequence = currentSequence;
     numOfLongestSequence = prev;
}
```

So, the final code will look like:
```java
import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println(&quot;Search for longest sequence: &quot;);
    Scanner s = new Scanner(System.in);
    int value;
    int prev = 0;
    int numOfLongestSequence = 0;
    int longestSequence = 1;
    int currentSequence = 0;

    while (s.hasNextInt() &amp;&amp; (value = s.nextInt()) != 0) {

      if (prev == 0) {
        prev = value;
        // initialize the current sequence.
        currentSequence = 1;
        continue;
      }
      if (value == prev) {
        currentSequence++;
      } else {
        if (currentSequence &gt; longestSequence) {
          longestSequence = currentSequence;
          numOfLongestSequence = prev;
        }
        currentSequence = 1;
      }
      prev = value;
    }

    // check for longest sequence
    if (currentSequence &gt; longestSequence) {
      longestSequence = currentSequence;
      numOfLongestSequence = prev;
    }
    System.out.println(&quot;Longest sequence: &quot; + longestSequence + &quot; times &quot; + numOfLongestSequence);
  }
}
```

